nodes.description: Retrieve comprehensive information about linked lists from the internet.
nodes.agent_prompt: Gather detailed information about linked lists, including their definition, types, advantages, disadvantages, common operations (insertion, deletion, traversal), and applications. Include code examples in Python, Java, and C++ where applicable.

nodes.description: Synthesize the information retrieved about linked lists, highlighting key aspects and comparing different implementations.
nodes.agent_prompt: Synthesize the information about linked lists from the provided source. Focus on creating a cohesive and well-structured summary that covers the definition, types, advantages, disadvantages, common operations, and applications of linked lists. Compare and contrast different implementations in Python, Java, and C++. Identify the strengths and weaknesses of each implementation. Explain the time and space complexity of each operation.

nodes.description: Format the synthesized information into a well-structured and human-readable report.
nodes.agent_prompt: Format the synthesized information about linked lists into a comprehensive and easy-to-understand report. Use headings, subheadings, bullet points, tables, and code examples to present the information clearly. Include an introduction, a detailed explanation of linked lists, examples of code, and a conclusion.
